{
  "stem": "4513.1",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] And my sister was-- my older sister became a Lutheran.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "So we belonged to all sorts of religious groups because it was not-- it was not the first religion of my family.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "My family, being Seminoles, had the religion of Native Americans at the time, and all the rest of these things were sort of superimposed on us.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "So they learned to live compatibly with it, but I don't think they learned to accept it or take it in as a-- as a-- as a deep, intrinsic, philosophical thing for themselves.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, we still believe that the great spirit was in the trees, in the forest.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We believe that-- and basically, you believe that all human beings are human beings, and that there is no difference in people, regardless of what they look like, as long as they're human beings.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And all human beings are alike.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And that the animals of the world are-- are not far from human beings.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They interact with human beings, and they-- they do things to help human beings.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And some of them were sacred to us.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Eagles were sacred.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And there were some other things that I don't remember now that were sacred to us.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "But the idea of God being in the trees and all the great father being in the trees and being in the-- in the grass and being-- and that one ought to always respect the natural things around us and not to destroy them wantonly.",
      "word_count": 45
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "One of the great tragedies I think the Indians suffered in America was the Indians believe you live-- whatever-- whatever mother nature delivers up, you live-- you try to live compatible with it.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "You don't change it.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "You don't sweep it away.",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
